    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i tried a log transform but the residuals still look kind of wonky. they seem to cluster in a way that doesn't look like a standard bell curve, almost like there's some underlying pattern or systematic error happening in those specific high-value segments. do you think i should look into heteroscedasticity or try a different error distribution entirely?",
