      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the residuals still show a pattern rather than just general non-normality, you should definitely investigate heteroscedasticity, which is the non-constant variance across levels of the predictors. You could test for this using Breusch-Pagan or White tests, and if present, use Weighted Least Squares (WLS) to account for the varying error magnitudes. If the patterns persist, switching to a generalized linear model (GLM) with an appropriate error distribution, like Gamma, might be necessary.",
      "source": "target",
